OL,7,F"There was no cause of death.
OL,9,F"His heart rhythm just stopped - it
OL,10,Fjust turned off."
OL,12,F"One in 300 people we screen will be
OL,13,Fidentified with a potentially life-
OL,14,Fthreatening cardiac condition," Dr
OL,15,FSteven Cox, CEO of Cardiac Risk in the
OL,16,FYoung, said.
OL,18,F"Once they are identified there are
OL,19,Ftreatments, lifestyle advice and
OL,20,Fsometimes even corrective surgery. Sue
OL,21,Fhas already held her first screening.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/7
